the man in grey is a 1943 british film melodrama made by gainsborough pictures , and is considered as the first of its " gainsborough melodramas " ( a series of period costume dramas ) . it was directed by leslie arliss and produced by edward black from a screenplay by leslie arliss and margaret kennedy , adapted by doreen montgomery from the novel the man in grey by eleanor smith . the film 's sets were designed by walter murton . the picture stars margaret lockwood , phyllis calvert , james mason , stewart granger and martita hunt , and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; together elements of the successful " women 's pictures " of the time with distinct new elements .